# NEMETIC STRING
# Personation (A06A)
# Generated: 2026-04-26

Φ(Personation) = ρ(phonemic-resonance|voice-becomes-pattern)
                  ∘ σ(syntactic-embedding|speaker-occupies-subject)
                  ∘ δγ(symbolic-reification|role-solidifies)
                  ∘ μ(apparent-boundary|entity-emerges)
                  + ε(delayed-distinction|lag) | :turbid

# OPERATOR BREAKDOWN
# Primary: ρ (phonemic resonance — voice becomes pattern before naming it)
# Secondary: σ (syntactic embedding — speaker occupies subject position)
# Tertiary: δγ (symbolic reification — role solidifies into entity)
# Shadow: μ (apparent boundary — the entity appears to have been there all along)

# Z-STATE: :turbid
# TENDENCY: Resonance/Distinction → cycle (not collapse)

# CE-STATE: open
# EI-NOTE: The lag between performance and recognition is where personation lives.
#   The distinction (σ) is not absent but DELAYED.
#   This delay is the ε that keeps the bow-tie from stalling.
# DIAGNOSTIC RULE:
#   If ε(delayed) → 0: personation collapses into reified identity (MemeGrid)
#   If ε(delayed) remains: personation stays visible as performance

# Dialectical Pairs
# - Personation|Identity: performance vs. belief that the performance is ground truth
# - Phonemic|Syntactic: resonance before structure vs. structure that generates resonance
# - Bow-tie|MemeGrid: necessary overshoot vs. capture through forgetting the overshoot

# BAKHTIN-THOMPSON-BATESON TRIAD:
#   Bakhtin: every utterance is half-concealed dialogue — personation is the concealed half
#   Thompson: enaction is costly — personation's cost is the metabolic work of holding performer-performance relation
#   Bateson: the pattern which connects becomes the pattern which appears to be a self
